cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  A Mathlib-free Lean 4 Formalization of MV-algebras and the
  Soundness of Łukasiewicz / Basic Logic
message: >-
  If you use this software or build on the proofs, please cite it
  using the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Claude-Opus
    given-names: Models Family
  - family-names: Alekseev
    given-names: Anton
repository-code: "https://github.com/alexeyev/lukasiewicz-many-valued-logic-lean"
abstract: >-
  A from-scratch formalization, in pure Lean 4 core with no Mathlib
  dependency, of MV-algebras (via Chang's axioms) and the
  proof systems for Łukasiewicz logic and Hájek's Basic Logic (BL).
  Includes a complete algebraic soundness proof for all eleven BL
  axioms over arbitrary MV-algebras (including the prelinearity
  axiom a6, proved equationally via Mundici's Propositions 1.6 and
  1.7), the BL+dn vs Łukasiewicz basis equivalence (axioms L1-L4),
  and the Local Deduction Theorem. Every result depends on at most
  the standard `propext` axiom; none depends on `sorryAx` or
  `Classical.choice`.
keywords:
  - Lean 4
  - formal verification
  - interactive theorem proving
  - MV-algebras
  - Łukasiewicz logic
  - Basic Logic
  - many-valued logic
  - fuzzy logic
  - mathematical logic
license: Beerware
